	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=74761><span id= >Balnore</span></a><br><span id=notbold>99 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.45]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I think there is a happy medium or maybe being a boy-scout helps as a warrior. AKA always be prepared.&nbsp;&nbsp;Overall, my AC is decent at 650 at 26th level, hps are barely sub 1k, both unbuffed, while my resists are really good due to the choice of gear that also adds some stats like the blackend alloy helm or something that has great resists.  What I mean by being prepared is that I use 10AC rings that have the downside of neg 7 magic resist for everyday situations of non-casting mobs (neg 14 is tough against casters). However, I have two 4ac 45hp rings in my inventory that I can switch out when I hear adherant incoming (assuming I'm not pulling) or use if I am pulling casters.  In that same backpack I carry two 25 cha steins used when buying and selling from NPCs and my 2hander for practice situations.<br><br>I realize not everybody can afford dual sets of slots but like me, as you get new items that have downsides to them, keep your old ones.  Sure I'm a bit heavy but that's what str is for.  My 2cp and I don't know everything for sure so take it with a grain of salt.  Hope this helps somebody.<br><br>Balner</p>&nbsp;<br>Davidon<br>Wood Elf Druid<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=547810" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=547810</a><br><br>Sinfonian<br>Half-Elf Bard<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=547835" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=547835</a></td></td></tr>
