	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=64677><span id=Sage>xaanru</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>1339 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.83]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>True, there are situations where SAVES mean as much as ac. However, since crusty armor is not loaded with saves, and has a bunch of melee stats, it often tempts new warriors into choosing it over higher ac items, or ones with HP. <br><br>For my warrior, I pick items with the following things AC (#1 thing), HP (2nd), and Saves (3rd). I have some resist items I can use in situations where I'm expecting a lot of magic damage, but for the typical grind situation, AC/HP are king and queen.<br><br>The only other stats you should worry about is get sta over 100, so no worries on weapon weight, and AGI, because it adds HP. People always want high STR, which isn't NEARLY as important as the other stats.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Aug 19 10:22:07 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
